        • [ - ] GioMonaldo - member since 26-Sep-18

          The rating system is flawed, but not for the reasons these Messi hating losers are spouting here. It is flawed bc it gives too much importance to attacking actions, especially assists and goals, and too little importance to defensive actions. If a forward can win MOTM for scoring and assisting, then a defender or a GK should be able to win MOTM for some equally important last man tackles or crucial interceptions. We should be able to see a more even distribution of MOTM awards between forwards and defenders and we should definitely be able to see the occasional perfect 10 for GKs as well. If a GK saves 3 great on goal shots, then he's had a contribution equivalent to scoring a hat-trick. I mean has a GK ever got perfect 10 rating on this site?
